{"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib"]]},"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"platforms":["macOS"],"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"protocol"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"StringChunkProtocol"},{"kind":"text","text":" : "},{"text":"PointerWrapper","kind":"typeIdentifier","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/PointerWrapper","preciseIdentifier":"s:4GLib14PointerWrapperP"}],"languages":["swift"]}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"level":2,"text":"Overview","type":"heading","anchor":"overview"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"String chunks are used to store groups of strings. Memory is","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"allocated in blocks, and as strings are added to the "},{"code":"GStringChunk","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"they are copied into the next free position in a block. When a block"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"is full a new block is allocated."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"When storing a large number of strings, string chunks are more"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"efficient than using [func","type":"text"},{"code":"GLib.strdup","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"] since fewer calls to "},{"code":"malloc()","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"are needed, and less memory is wasted in memory allocation overheads."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"By adding strings with [method"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GLib.StringChunk.insert_const"},{"type":"text","text":"] it is also"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"possible to remove duplicates."}]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"To create a new ","type":"text"},{"code":"GStringChunk","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" use [func"},{"code":"GLib.StringChunk.new","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":"].","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"To add strings to a "},{"code":"GStringChunk","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" use [method","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GLib.StringChunk.insert"},{"type":"text","text":"]."}]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"To add strings to a ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GStringChunk"},{"type":"text","text":", but without duplicating strings"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"which are already in the ","type":"text"},{"code":"GStringChunk","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":", use [method","type":"text"},{"code":"GLib.StringChunk.insert_const","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"]."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"To free the entire "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GStringChunk"},{"type":"text","text":" use [method"},{"code":"GLib.StringChunk.free","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":"].","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"It is not possible to free individual strings."}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StringChunkProtocol","isActive":true},{"text":" protocol exposes the methods and properties of an underlying ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"GStringChunk"},{"type":"text","text":" instance."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"The default implementation of these can be found in the protocol extension below.","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"For a concrete class that implements these methods and properties, see "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StringChunk","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":"."},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"Alternatively, use "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StringChunkRef","isActive":true},{"text":" as a lighweight, ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"unowned"},{"text":" reference if you already have an instance you just want to use.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"abstract":[{"code":"GStringChunk","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" provides efficient storage of groups of strings","type":"text"}],"sections":[],"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StringChunkProtocol","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/glib\/stringchunkprotocol"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"minor":3,"patch":0},"kind":"symbol","metadata":{"navigatorTitle":[{"text":"StringChunkProtocol","kind":"identifier"}],"role":"symbol","symbolKind":"protocol","roleHeading":"Protocol","modules":[{"name":"GLib"}],"title":"StringChunkProtocol","externalID":"s:4GLib19StringChunkProtocolP","fragments":[{"text":"protocol","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"StringChunkProtocol","kind":"identifier"}]},"relationshipsSections":[{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/PointerWrapper"],"type":"inheritsFrom","kind":"relationships","title":"Inherits From"},{"title":"Conforming Types","identifiers":["doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StringChunk","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StringChunkRef"],"type":"conformingTypes","kind":"relationships"}],"topicSections":[{"anchor":"Instance-Methods","title":"Instance Methods","identifiers":["doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StringChunkProtocol\/clear()","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StringChunkProtocol\/free()","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StringChunkProtocol\/insert(string:)","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StringChunkProtocol\/insertConst(string:)","doc:\/\/GLib\/documentation\/GLib\/StringChunkProtocol\/insertLen(string:len:)"],"generated":true}],"references":{"doc://GLib/documentation/GLib/PointerWrapper":{"fragments":[{"text":"protocol","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"PointerWrapper"}],"kind":"symbol","abstract":[{"t